Reasoning: The paper deals with image recognition systems and learning image representations that minimize information leakage, which are topics typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of adversarial non-zero sum games and entropy as a measure of information content suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the datasets used in the numerical experiments (UCI, Extended Yale B, CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100) are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
